<Layout
	title="About"
	description="Who I am and where this is going."
	pubDate={new Date('July 11 2026')}
>
	<p>
		I'm Jonah. I work in IT at TerraPower, a nuclear energy R&amp;D company. It's my first IT
		job. The title says Tier 1–2 support; the work stopped matching the title a while ago.
	</p>

	<p>
		The enterprise half of the job is Active Directory and M365 administration: onboarding,
		offboarding, security groups, license lifecycle, auditing. When I started, the team ran on
		one-off scripts nobody could safely rerun. The tooling now has input validation, dry-run
		modes, structured logging, and lives in version control with a change-review process — all
		of which I introduced. I also wrote the guide that got technicians with no programming
		background using Git, because tooling nobody adopts is just a repo.
	</p>

	<p>
		The lab side of the job — cRIO controllers, LabVIEW experiment rigs, instruments,
		air-gapped machines, experiments that run 24/7 — turned out to be the part I actually
		like. I've been building that support function into something deliberate: asset inventory,
		decision frameworks, a technician training path, and a Purdue-model classification of lab
		assets to find the security gaps. That's the direction everything here bends: OT/IT
		convergence, with GICSP as the next milestone. Not aspiring to it. Already doing the
		unglamorous first parts of it.
	</p>

	<p>
		Off the clock I run a roleplay-PVP Project Zomboid server with my friend ATPot. Ninety-odd
		mods, a managed host with SFTP-only access, and real players finding real bugs. Most of
		the projects on this site came out of keeping that world alive.
	</p>

	<p>
		I use AI tooling heavily and openly. It writes a lot of first drafts; I catch its bugs and
		it catches mine. The judgment calls stay human. That's stated once, here, and assumed
		everywhere else on the site.
	</p>

	<p>
		There's also a personal finance dashboard that pulls live bank data over MCP into a local
		browser page. It works, and it stays private, which is the whole point of it.
	</p>

	<p>
		I'm on GitHub as <a href="https://github.com/docrickman">docrickman</a>.
	</p>
</Layout>
